<br>
So is there a need for PR? or is it affective? <br>
<br>
As well, this board does not speak for the FV community, but only those who frequent the board. Many players, some by choice, avoid these boards, recognizing them as an unreliable source of information or smut. And if you or your guild is of this belief, does this mean you have bad PR? If you are the nicest person/player in the world but people flame you on the FV board does that make you disliked? Maybe so, but that's just sad.<br>
<br>
My suggestion, if you read the board, take into consideration the source and make an effort to form your own opinions about people and organizations. PR should be in game, not in flame. <br>
<br>
the Venerable John Falstaff<br>
