<br>
For the person, if you see a lot of postings, good or ill, you still would develop an opinion about the person and thus of the character.  How many of us have an opinion good and bad of people here based on the board?  I know I do.  I have even looked for specific people in the game because of their posts here (well, noted them on my track or in the zone /who) and gone out of my way to say hello (&amp; for a shy person, that can be tough).<br>
<br>
For guilds, if you continue to see the same guild tag on a certain calibre of post, you would begin to regard that guild with your opinion associated with those posts.  I, for one, sought out Saga in large part because I saw the Saga tag on postings -here- that I thought were made by people I would like to associate with.  I don't mean I agreed with every posting, just I thought I would be in good stead with them.  The other guilds I was looking at in my quest also have members who post here and I felt kindly about them as well, but not so strongly as I did for Saga. I sought to meet Saga based solely on the reputation, the PR if you will, presented on the FV boards.  I'm glad I did *grin*.<br>
<br>
